rComments: An amazing professor! He's super funny and made every class interesting and fun! He knows what he is talking about and knows how to teach it to you. Definitely will be taking more classes with professor Saleh!

Prof Saleh was definitely one of my favourites, his lectures were amazinggg - they were interesting, funny, and interactive. He didn't just reiterate the readings because he knew we paid to be there. Note that you HAVE to do the readings. He said his goal was for his students to be interested and gain knowledge. He's also very approachable.
Would highly recommend taking his course. Easy A!

Prof Saleh is the best professor I've er had evthroughout my undergrad degree. His lectures are always interesting, NEVER BORING. He engages with course text and popular culture news all the time which usually consists of funny stories. More importantly above all that is he constantly encourages to reach out for help and use on-campus resources!

The best prof i've had at this school HANDS DOWN! His lectures and personality are something special. He is always telling stories, making jokes and at the end you have still learned so much. His tests are fair as long as you attend lecture! Take his course, you will not regret it

Walid was one of the best professors I have had at university. His lectures are fun and engaging. He doesn't just teach, he tells a story and that makes a huge difference in a 2 hour lecture. His tests are extremely fair and give you the opportunity to do well and show case what you know. However to do well you HAVE to attend lectures and read!

Dr. Saleh is the best professor I have ever had. I made the mistake of not taking more of his classes. He changed my life with the knowledge and perspectives I learned in his class. We are blessed to have him at this University. Just wow. And he deserves a chili pepper. Take his classes if you want to become a smarter person.
He gives hints about what will be on the quiz. Had him for RLG100y1
Love him! Fave prof. Walid please marry me

Professr Saleh was and is the most influential professor that I have personally have had.  He is passionate about his material and will go out of his way to explain and clarify (if you ask the right questions!)  He is the man who inspired me to venture into the field of religion, and for that I thank him.  It was a honor to learn from him.
ONE OF THE BEST PROFS AT UofT - SAINT GEORGE! kNows his material, and explains it very well.

Ok so no matter what people comaplain about him but he is definitely one of the best profs around. He knows so much about what he is talking about and does not move on until sure tht it's perfectly clear. The best part about his classes was the personal touch he added to them, his stories were alwys so interesting. HE WAS AN AWESOME PROF HANDS DOWN

It is essential to attend Prof. Saleh's lectures, as he goes above and beyond what is in the textbook. His class is definitely not easy, but it is possible to get an A+ if you really put the work in. His tests tend to be long and involved. He himself is very amusing, and his lectures are interesting.
Prof Saleh has a sexy accent and mind. Very intelligent, makes you think. Not just a religion course.

He tries to teach students as much as possible. He helps students prepare for the GREs and the real world. He is funny. He was very helpful to me outside the class. But, the grading system is messed up BIG TIME. No chance of getting an A+. His lectures were hard to follow. If you ask him a personal question, he will go crazy! But I love him.
interesting

An intelligent and articulate speaker. Nonetheless he is profoundly unhelpful with regards to individual student queries, often times repeating the refrain: "I'm sorry, I don't know what you want me to say" or "I can't help you with this." In person, he is cold, disinterested, and easily distracted. Not the friendliest professor out there.

This is the best course and prof I've had so far (in 2 years)! I love Saleh! He's not one of those high-mided profs who try and make their course and exams as difficult as possible. He's also very funny, and sweet! He makes everything so interesting. I miss him!
Very knowledgeable. I enjoyed his class. His lectures are so distilled .  He is also very funny, and engaging. He knows how to keep a first year class entertained.
I loved this course! Lectures are anything but boring- Saleh knows how to keep his students interested and happy. He's also incredibly sweet. Great prof, great course.

He's a very funny prof, so even though I don't like the material that much, the lectures are great. He can be annoying with skipping breaks sometimes though, and teaching right up til 8.

Definitely one of my fave profs. He was very funny, a good lecturer, and clearly told students what was expected of them in terms of tests and the final exam. I'd love to take another class taught by him.

I really enjoyed his class, as I found the tangents he goes off on very interesting. Also, he is so passionate about the material, it's infectious.  I would definitely take another class he's teaching.  Only drawback was that his accent sometimes makes it somewhat difficult to understand him.
Not really available out of class for much material help, but was nice for whatever limited contact I did have.
Very good lecturer!!!very fun and makes it relavent to today. I really enjoyed his class and would take another. NOT HELPFUL OUT OF THE CLASS ROOM!!!!!!!!
A funny and intelligent teacher. He did go off on tangents but during late night courses they were often helpful in keeping me awake. I really loved his class.
